Title: A clipse of my province
DateModified: '2019-03-12'
DatePublished: '2019-03-12'
Url: https://www.worldnomads.com/create/scholarships/writing/2019/applications/a-clipse-of-my-province
SetInCountry: South Africa
Category: Making a local connection
AuthorName: Nolungelo Shongwe
AuthorCountry: South Africa
Text: "The world is full of soo much potential and has soo many offers at hand,in\
  \ a world where my aprovince-Mpumalanga has it's own Top destinations and cultural\
  \ diversity.A connection is made when aspiring individuals  come together to experience\
  \ the beauty of nature,as well as activities  all at once.The landscapes do not\
  \ only have the big fives(wildlife) but also hospitality and some adrenaline to\
  \ get you on the go,there's  more to it,not only does it come with exceptional \
  \ hospitality ,the mountains and sunrise will make you feel brand new.\n\nMpumalanga\
  \ meaning the rising sun has  best cuisines and  cultural ankaras,from beadwork,sculpting,moulding\
  \ clay to sustaining and attracting tourist,traditional dances and symbolism of\
  \ crafts kept for specific occassions and how youngsters as well as elders interact\
  \ with each other.\n\nMpumalanga is a vast area that has Blyde River Canyon, which\
  \ is the third largest canyon on Earth.The Panorama Route is where you find your\
  \ God\u2019s Window,geological route surrounded by the Makhonjwa  Mountain which\
  \ is a heritage site,Bourke's Luck Potholes  just to name a few.\nMpumalanga is\
  \ also home to some of the oldest caves in the world, the Sudwala Caves.\nBe prepared\
  \ for a little walk though, its a beautiful experience that's worth it."
